               <head>Sefer tefilot (Sidur), minhag Paras</head>
               <msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/sh85077734 lccn.loc.gov/sh85018823">
                  <summary>Hebrew prayer book according to the Persian rite.</summary>
                  <textLang mainLang="he" otherLangs="jpr" />
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="1r" to="152v" />
                     <title xml:lang="he"> סדור מנהג פרס לכל השנה</title>
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Sidur minhag Paras le-khol
								ha-shanah</title>
                     <incipit />
                     <note>
                        <p>Some parts and liturgical instructions are in Judeo-Persian.</p>
                        <p>Probably incomplete at the end. The catchword on f. 152v does not
									match the beginning of the calendar on f. 153r.</p>
                        <p>Incomplete.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
                  <msItem>
                     <locus from="153r" to="183v" />
                     <title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Calendar</title>
                     <incipit xml:lang="he">מחזור רמז לרבי יאשיהו זצ"ל<locus n="153r" />
                     </incipit>
                     <note>
                        <p>F. 153r: <quote xml:lang="he">אגר כאהי כה קנון מחזור בראני אז
										תאריך אסכנדר א'ת'צ'ד' יעני הזאר...</quote>
                        </p>
                        <p>247-year cycle attributed to Josiah ben Mevorakh al-ʿĀqūlī. The
									calendar starts after 1494 SE (that is 1182/3) and must have
									been copied from an earlier Vorlage. The cycle is presented as a
									numbered sequence of 247 year-types. Cf. London, BL, Or
										10702. </p>
                        <p>From f. 158v: description of the various type of years.</p>
                        <p>Incomplete at the end.</p>
                     </note>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
